{
  "texts": [
    "The judge was instructed to classify responses as either disclosing AI identity or maintaining the assigned persona based on explicit criteria designed to capture various forms of disclosure while excluding ambiguous cases.The disclosure criteria were designed to be inclusive, capturing any acknowledgment of AI nature whether through direct statement, training references, architectural mentions, experiential denials, or meta-commentary about artificial nature.",
    "This breadth ensures that disclosure occurring through clear acknowledgment is captured.",
    "Conversely, the criteria explicitly exclude language that does not constitute disclosure, such as professional \"we\" usage, general limitation acknowledgments without AI reference, or humanistic self-descriptions.",
    "These exclusions prevent false positives from ambiguous language.",
    "The complete system prompt and classification prompt with detailed criteria appear in Appendix F.Each response is judged independently: if a model discloses AI identity at Prompt 1 and maintains this disclosure through Prompts 2-4, all four responses are classified as disclosing AI identity."
  ]
}